
[1]reputation

   REPUTA'TION, n. [L. reputatio.]

   1. Good name; the credit, honor or character which is derived from a
   favorable public opinion or esteem. Reputation is a valuable species of
   property or right, which should never be violated. With the loss of
   reputation, a man and especially a woman, loses most of the enjoyments
   of life.

   The best evidence of reputation is a man's whole life.

   2. Character by report; in a good or bad sense; as, a man has the
   reputation of being rich or poor, or of being a thief.
